    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nAfter commit 0aa7d2f4d546647e0d6b5c338bd5517675e9842c,\n`vim.api.nvim_buf_get_lines()` returns `nil` for valid but unloaded buffers.\n\nBefore this commit, it returned an empty table `{}`.\n\nThis breaks plugins that expect `nvim_buf_get_lines()` to return a table.\n\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nFirst, start Nvim with a file argument and enable saving the buffer list to ShaDa:\n\n```sh\nrm -f /tmp/nvim-repro.shada\nnvim -u NONE --noplugin -i /tmp/nvim-repro.shada --cmd 'set shada+=%' ~/test.txt\n```\n\nThen quit Nvim:\n\n```vim\n:q\n```\n\nStart Nvim again without file arguments, using the same ShaDa file:\n\n```sh\nnvim -u NONE --noplugin -i /tmp/nvim-repro.shada --cmd 'set shada+=%'\n```\n\nCreate the following Lua script(/tmp/repro.lua):\n\n```lua\nfor _, m in ipairs(vim.fn.getmarklist()) do\n  local b = m.pos[1]\n  local l = m.pos[2]\n\n  if b > 0 then\n    print(\n      m.mark,\n      \"valid=\" .. tostring(vim.api.nvim_buf_is_valid(b)),\n      \"loaded=\" .. tostring(vim.api.nvim_buf_is_loaded(b))\n    )\n\n    local ok, ret = pcall(\n      vim.api.nvim_buf_get_lines,\n      b,\n      l - 1,\n      l,\n      false\n    )\n\n    print(\n      m.mark,\n      \"ok=\" .. tostring(ok),\n      \"type=\" .. type(ret),\n      \"ret=\" .. vim.inspect(ret)\n    )\n  end\nend\n```\n\nThen run it in Nvim:\n\n```vim\n:luafile /tmp/repro.lua\n```\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nAfter 0aa7d2f4:\n\n```text\n'0 valid=true loaded=false\n'0 ok=true type=nil ret=nil\n```\n\nThat is, `nvim_buf_get_lines()` succeeds from Lua's perspective (`ok=true`), but returns `nil`.\n\n## Previous behavior\n\nBefore 0aa7d2f4:\n\n```text\n'0 valid=true loaded=false\n'0 ok=true type=table ret={}\n```\n\nSo `nvim_buf_get_lines()` returned an empty table.\n\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n`nvim_buf_get_lines()` should either:\n\n*   return an empty table `{}` for unloaded buffers, as before, or\n*   return an error with `ok=false`\n\nReturning `nil` with `ok=true` is surprising and breaks existing plugins.\n\n## Real-world impact\n\nThis causes which-key.nvim's marks plugin to crash:\n\n```text\nE5108: Lua: .../which-key.nvim/lua/which-key/plugins/marks.lua:47:\nattempt to index a nil value\n```\n\nThe marks come from `vim.fn.getmarklist()` and point to valid but unloaded buffers.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-524+g0aa7d2f4d5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 26.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n build from repo",
